data.name: Family Adventure Path
data.longDescription:
Be prepared for lots of adventures on your hike ....

Follow the tracks of the grizzly bear. It’s the only way to reach the Land of the Native Americans. Be on guard and try to solve the mystery.



White Bird, the chieftain of the HANSA-PARK Native Americans says:

“Always remember that alone a warrior
can’t fight the dangers lurking in the prairie.
A warrior is only strong if he is supported by the people of his tribe.
“Together” is the only way to face the evil and the dangers and win.”


White Bird is very wise and knows a lot because he has led a life full of adventures. Listen to the well-meaning advice of the old chieftain and you will solve the mystery of the bear...
data.shortDescription: Be prepared for lots of adventures on your hike ....
data.metaDescription: Walk the Family Adventure Path and be in for lots of adventures. Follow the tracks of the grizzly bear and try to solve the mystery.

themeworlds.name: Adventure Land
themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.name: Adventure Ship "Käpt'n Orki"
data.longDescription:
Climbing and exploring in true Hanseatic style

You won’t find any precious treasures and secrets if you walk on beaten tracks with hordes of other people. Go on a discovery tour and explore the adventure ships - on your own or with a few trustworthy mates. You may be lucky.
data.shortDescription: Climbing and exploring in true Hanseatic style
data.metaDescription: Explore the adventure ship "Käpt'n Orki" at HANSA-PARK where climbing and exploring is real fun!
data.rideDescription: Crab cutter with steep stairs, narrow paths that lead through the fuselage and a steering wheel that invites to play with. Use at own risk.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Awilda’s Adventure Ride
data.longDescription: NEW 2021: Awilda’s Adventure Ride - the new, lovingly designed water ride right next to Störtebeker's Sea Raid is the 6th water ride at HANSA-PARK. Any child that is at least 90cm tall can hop on if an adult accompanies them. What are you waiting for? Climb into the barrels and off you go!

data.rideDescription:
Boat ride featuring two deep drops. Ride includes periods of darkness with light and sound effects.
If the boats come to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use a steep ramp at a maximum of appr. 3 meters height.

data.name: Awilda’s Lookout
data.longDescription:
[nbsp]

NEW: Awilda’s Lookout is HANSA-PARK’s third free-fall tower, each of which has its own fan community. Adrenaline junkies love the HIGHLANDER - the tallest and fastest gyro drop tower in the world, the tiniest tots enjoy Odin's Travels through the Sky, and those who prefer a fast-paced ride with lots of twists will definitely go for the new 11m-tall ride, Awilda’s Lookout.

data.rideDescription: Vertical ride with sudden drops. If the gondola stops after the ride has started, riders must wait for the operating staff’s instructions before they are allowed to exit the ride. At the worst, the ride may stop at the highest position, i.e. over 8 m up in the air. Passengers may have to exit having to use a manlift at a maximum of appr. 8 meters height. This process may take up to 20 minutes.

Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

All day long!

data.longDescription: Barcos del Mar - A fabulous combination of ship and motorcycle. Eight motorcycles including ship’s tender, built from flotsam and jetsam, take off in a circle. Each one can be controlled individually. Biker Captains taller than 90cm can take a ride right opposite the Tienda del Mar.
data.shortDescription: Barcos del Mar - eine wundervolle Kombination aus Schiff und Motorrad. Acht Motorräder samt Beiboot, aus Strandgut zusammengebaut, heben kreisförmig ab und können ganz individuell gesteuert werden. Gleich gegenüber der Tienda del Mar dürfen Bikerkapitäne bereits ab einer Körpergröße von 90 cm die Fahrt antreten.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

themeworlds.name: Lumberjacks' Camp
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Face the demon from Russia. Be catapulted into the air. Emerge from the horror of old walls towards the sky. After the ride: Pale. Numb. Ecstatic. Not everyone manages that.

Don’t you dare, Mr Escape of Novgorod!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Face the demon from Russia. Be catapulted into the air. Emerge from the horror of old walls towards the sky.

After the ride: Pale. Numb. Ecstatic.

Not everyone manages that.

Don’t you dare, Mr Escape of Novgorod!

data.name: Barracuda Slide
data.longDescription:
Race down the blue slides on a water bobsled. It takes courage to plunge from a height of 12 metres.

A really splashy affair!

Barracuda – the “dangerous” name does justice to North Germany’s first wavy water ride featuring four lanes where riders are propelled down at lightning speed like a barracuda. Don’t worry - most of the time you’ll stay dry.

data.name: Apache Lodge Tree House
data.longDescription:
Our Apache Lodge is a spectacular tree house more than 10m above the ground that’s waiting for climbers to conquer it.

Anyone who wants to reach the tree house must climb through a huge tree trunk. Once on top, all big and small Apaches must be courageous enough to step out onto the balcony of the Apache Lodge to enter the rambling house high up in the tree. From there you can only leave the tree house after a challenging climb and carefully feeling your way across a 25m-long, swaying suspension bridge. [nbsp]

Be prepared to crawl up on all fours if you want to follow your children and explore the tree house…
data.shortDescription: High up in the midst of nature
data.metaDescription: The Apache Lodge at HANSA-PARK is a spectacular tree house more than 10m above the ground that’s waiting for climbers to conquer it.
data.rideDescription:
The tree house and the suspension bridge are attractions according to the DIN EN 1176.

Use at own risk.

themeworlds.name: Adventure Land
themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.longDescription: Worked up an appetite riding the hypercoaster? Don’t worry - KÄRNAN is just a stone’s throw away from the Log Cabin where you can feed your empty stomach with delicious ice cream or a fresh pretzel!
data.shortDescription: Open at weekends, on bank/public holidays and in the school holidays.
data.metaDescription: Go to the Kungstorget Log Cabin to get cool-me-down ice cream, thirst-quenching drinks or fortifying pretzels.

data.name: "Flower Magic" Boat Tour
data.longDescription:
On the Rose Route the waves gently lap against the boat. Cheerful waltz music quietly fills the air, getting you in the mood for summer.

A relaxing boat tour through our sea of flowers at the Old-Time Fun Fair: hop in and glide peacefully through a world filled with the scent of flowers.

And during our Autumn Magic event, our special lighting will enhance the lovely charm of the mesmerising scenery.

data.rideDescription:

themeworlds.name: Old-Time Fun Fair
themeworlds.shortDescription: Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.

We captured the atmosphere of a nostalgic fairground and added some attractions: the Safari Jeeps, the Flying Dutchman and the Flower Magic Boat Tour.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

data.name: Bodega del Mar
data.longDescription:
Open during the summer and autumn holidays.

Our Bodega is located on the Plaza del Mar. In fine weather the brilliant view of the glittering Baltic Sea from the terrace is a real treat for the eyes.
data.shortDescription: Open during the summer and autumn holidays.
data.metaDescription: Bodega, Spain, Plaza del Mar, terrace, Baltic Sea, snack, drinks
keywords: You’ll find the Bodega at HANSA-PARK’s Plaza del Mar. In fine weather you’ll enjoy a fabulous view of the Baltic Sea from its terrace.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Pretzel Shop
data.longDescription: Our Pretzel Shop offers any kind of freshly baked lye rolls you can think of, from traditional pretzels all the way to Mexico rolls. For those with a sweet tooth: How about an ice-cream for the way home?
data.shortDescription: Open from 2 pm.
data.metaDescription: The Pretzel Shop not only offers any kind of freshly baked pretzels you can think of, but various baked goods such as baguette rolls, bread and spicy snacks as well.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Letter Box
data.longDescription:
You’ll find a letter box at the arcades close to our HANSE-KONTOR. Look for a large brown treasure chest.

Make sure that your mail has sufficient postage before you place it into the letter box. We will affix our special HANSA-PARK stamp and send it off the next day…

data.name: Bronze Sea Lions
data.longDescription: You need to get away from the hustle and bustle in the Park? Take a break at our Hansa Garden while the little guests have fun with the bronze sea lions. An oasis of peace right in the heart of the Park!
data.shortDescription: Located right next to our Hansa Swing Ride
data.metaDescription: Take a break in our Water Garden while the little guests have fun with the dancing water fountains next to the bronze sea lions.

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

data.name: Cinema Fantastico 4D
data.longDescription:
An absolutely fabulous highlight in crystal-clear digital projection.

Lots of special effects make the films at our 4D cinema, which are shown several times a day, exciting and funny but be prepared for some goose bumps too.

Pursuant to section 12 in connection with section 14 German Youth Protection Act [Jugendschutzgesetz] in Schleswig-Holstein "No Age Restrictions apply" to our film.


The shows at 11.30 am, 1.30 pm, 3.30 pm and 5.30 pm are in English.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Crazy Mine
data.longDescription:
In the land of the Gold Prospectors mine carts zig-zag their way deep into the shaft at breakneck speed. Welcome to the miners' world!

Right behind the tall shaft head frame you’ll find the access to Crazy Mine’s rock tunnel. While you are on your way to the mine-train loading station with the same name, you walk past mine scenes from the days of the gold rush in North America. Get into an authentic mine cart and go on a trip through dark tunnels into the gold diggers' world of the 19th century.
data.shortDescription: In the land of the Gold Prospectors mine carts zig-zag their way deep into the shaft at breakneck speed. Welcome to the miners' world!
data.metaDescription: The gold prospectors at HANSA-PARK are busy. Help them or take a ride in the Crazy Mine carts.
data.rideDescription:
Fast paced thrill ride with quick turns and sudden drops. Ride includes hard braking.

If the vehicles come to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 12 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 20 minutes.

themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.name: Crêperie
data.longDescription: Popular sweet snacks during a park visit are our crêpes. Try your “very own” crêpe creation; mix and match your individual crêpe according to your desire and taste. Of course, we also offer the traditional crêpe with cinnamon and sugar for you to take away and enjoy it at Hansa Garden.
data.shortDescription: A sweet snack for in between
data.metaDescription: Popular sweet snacks during a Park visit are our crêpes. Nobody can resist them!

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

data.name: The little Tsar
data.longDescription:
”The Little Tsar – my first roller coaster” is the perfect start into the adventure called roller coaster. Lovingly designed and woven into a story just like its bigger cousins at the Park, the attraction offers little guests roller coaster riding fun in the true style of HANSA-PARK. Accompanied by a melody specifically composed for the adorable Little Tsar, the first ride will be an experience your child will never forget.

[nbsp]

Our tip: Don’t forget your on-ride photo. The machine is located right behind the exit to your left.

You can, of course, have this special moment captured in a photo. At the ride exit you can get your personal on-ride photograph and take home a print copy right away, so you won’t ever forget your first time on a roller coaster…
data.shortDescription: Our new children’s roller coaster is fun for young and old alike

data.name: The Oath of KÄRNAN
data.longDescription:
The Oath of KÄRNAN - Beware of its spell!

With the launch of the family thrill ride “The Oath of KÄRNAN” in 2015 HANSA-PARK made roller coaster history: emerging from a 79m-high tower after a 67m first drop this hypercoaster speeds up to127 km/h on the 1,235m-long track. The reverse free fall from over 60m in the KÄRNAN tower is unique worldwide.

Since 2017 the worldwide unique reverse free fall in the dark has been even longer, more intense, more KÄRNAN -a true XXL experience! The free fall velocity rate has been more than doubled from about 5m/sec to roughly 11m/sec.

Be bound by the spell of KÄRNAN and experience a thrilling roller coaster ride with the whole family. Anyone taller than 130cm can hop on!

Visit us on YouTube!
data.shortDescription: The Oath of KÄRNAN - Beware of its spell!
data.metaDescription: The hypercoaster “The Oath of KÄRNAN” is Europe’s second highest coaster. The reverse free fall from over 60m in the KÄRNAN tower is unique worldwide.
data.rideDescription:
High speed roller coaster featuring sudden drops, vertical ascent, backward free-fall, vertical descent, quick turns and a heartline roll. Ride includes periods of darkness with light and sound effects.

If the train comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 73 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 45 minutes.
data.storyText:
The Legend of the Construction of KÄRNAN and the Origin of the Spell

Eons ago on a dark and moonless night in November, the old King of Denmark died an untimely death, stabbed by his closest confidants while hunting. He was succeeded on the throne by his son Erik, who was a mere 12 years old when he was crowned and began to rule over his father’s kingdom.

Erik swore his coronation oath -- and every oath thereafter during his reign-- “by all the holy men” -- ved alle hellige maend -- which earned him the name “Erik Menved”.

King Erik lived in tumultuous times. His father’s slayers had been banished. They became pirates who terrorized the coastal towns and villages of Denmark. They frightened the residents who feared for their homes and lives. But the young king was oblivious to the problems and worries of his subjects. Instead, he spent his time hosting costly and pompous tournaments and dreaming of conquering faraway countries.

Soon the King’s coffers began to run low as Erik sank deeper into his new lifestyle. He held even more costly tournaments than any king before him. When his funds were almost exhausted, he raised taxes and pledged parts of his kingdom to the nobles of other countries.

Then a famine broke out in Denmark, but the wasteful King refused to lower taxes. Instead, he had all uprisings put down and the rebellious peasants hanged in front of the city gates. He expected it to be a deterrent, but the nobles joined forces with the peasants and turned against the King. It was a massive rebellion, and King Erik was able to suppress it only with the help of foreign mercenaries.

Instead of acknowledging his errors, Erik felt threatened by his subjects and the neighboring kingdoms. He convened his court and proclaimed:

“Our enemies are lurking in the shadows and beyond our borders, but we will build a castle for ourselves and for Denmark -- a fortress so strong that our enemies will never be able to invade and destroy it! We swear, by all the holy men.”

The King summoned his old and wise master builder and entrusted him with the monumental task of building an invincible castle. The builder retreated to his chambers and remained there many months drawing plans for an enormous structure with a strong outer ring wall, a moat and drawbridge, countless defense works, and a king’s tower (“the keep”) larger and more majestic than the country had ever seen.

Inside the castle he planned for a splendid great hall for receptions, cozy private rooms, as well as spacious pantries and a deep well to ensure there would always be enough water and food for the castle inhabitants in the event of a siege. His life depended on it.

The crown jewel of the plan, however, was a cleverly thought out system of secret passageways in the walls of the fortress and a complex emergency system that would help the royal family escape, if need be.

When he saw the drawings, Erik Menved immediately realized his dream of becoming invincible was suddenly within his grasp. He ordered the construction of KÄRNAN to begin immediately.

The old master builder had seen many a king come and come during his long life -- both benevolent and cruel. But he had never experienced a king who placed his own well-being as far above that of his starving subjects as King Erik Menved did. While construction was progressing, the old man pondered how he could help the people of Denmark without breaking his oath to build an invincible fortress for the kingdom.

One night, while watching the inebriated King and his advisors playing dice and betting their riches, the master builder suddenly knew what to do. He hurried down to his archives and searched through the writings of his predecessors. He was looking for a special magic formula that would protect the tower while at the same time punishing the King for his cruelty and keeping him away from his people.

After seven years the tower was completed. The master builder stepped before Erik and said, “My King, the construction you ordered has been completed. The kingdom now has a fortress that is most likely unconquerable: KARNAN.”

King Erik Menved’s face froze. He fixed the master builder with a piercing stare. “Most likely unconquerable? Have I not publicly sworn and ordered you, under the penalty of death, to build a tower that is invincible forever and ever?”

“Yes, my Ruler, you certainly did. And this castle is more secure and stronger than any fortress ever built. Yet I do not dare mention a dangerous thing such as a protective spell in your presence.”

“Tell me about this protective spell that you have not mentioned to me,” the King demanded. “Would it make KÄRNAN invincible?”

“Yes, my King, that it would. But I must warn you: the old scriptures are a dangerous game. Their impact is high, but the price to pay may be higher still.” And he pulled out from his bag a large roll of parchment and carefully held it up. It was inscribed:

“Once read out loud, a powerful spell will be cast over the tower that will hit all those who intend to attack, threaten, or approach KÄRNAN with the air to conquer it. The spell will destroy them. My King, though this magic formula would make the fortress invincible, it comes with a high price!”

Greedily, King Erik Menved wrested the scroll from the canny old master builder. “I will pay it. I shall raise the taxes,” the King said. Little did he know that he would have to pay a much higher price when he, blinded by the prospect of power, uttered, “I will take the risk -- by all the holy men!”

He quickly unrolled the parchment and spoke the age-old magic formula to protect the tower. But with every word he spoke, it was as if a piece of his innermost soul was torn from him and flung towards the tower, penetrating its walls and sinking deep down to its core where the spell unfolded.

The King had hardly finished speaking when he looked as if he had aged by twenty or thirty years. His skin had become wrinkled and ashen, his glance unsteady and empty.

King Erik Menved died soon afterwards, but in death he had fulfilled his oath and given the kingdom an unconquerable fortress.

From then on, the design of the castle and the power of the spell protected KÄRNAN from all attacks and dangers. No army was able to conquer it. No enemy ever invaded it, and all those who tried met with misfortune and death.

The King, however, forced to protect KÄRNAN forever by the clever trick of the master builder, will find salvation only by an act of kindness he had never shown while still alive.

[nbsp]

data.name: Midgard Serpent
data.longDescription:
An exciting story:


Two children, the Viking boy Einar and his older sister Elin of the Viking settlement of Hedeby, sneak into the shed of a famous Nordic storyteller. In the shed there is a legendary dragon boat which they are familiar with from the poet’s stories. The poet always talked of seafaring and the many adventures he allegedly had on board the ship, of his trade trips to the Varangians, of coming face to face with Norwegian pirates, of his trips to Greenland and his journey to the end of the world and the Midgard Serpent. Suddenly people are approaching and the children hide in one of the sea boxes on the dragon boat. And all of a sudden, the magic ship starts to move....
data.shortDescription: Get Ready for the Family Adventure - Our family coaster "The Midgard Serpent" carries its passengers off into the legendary world of the Vikings.
data.metaDescription: Our family coaster the “Midgard Serpent” carries its passengers off into the legendary world of the Vikings.
data.rideDescription:
Fast paced roller coaster featuring periods of darkness with sound and light effects and pop up characters.

If the train comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 9 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 15 minutes.

data.name: Can Knockdown and Fishing for Prize Bags
data.longDescription:
Try your luck and catch a prize bag! If luck is on your side, you’ll catch the top prize and walk home with a huge soft toy.

And with just a bit of extra skill you can score a strike in the Can Knockdown and choose a fabulous prize.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

data.name: Dr Livingstone’s Safari-Flight
data.longDescription:
For bush pilots on a mission and those who want to become a bush pilot. The drum is calling.

A very special attraction for all children at the Old-Time Fun Fair: the very small and bigger pilots can fly the African explorer planes themselves and every now and then land on a small lake. Don't worry - the machines are seaplanes with real floats.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Family Restaurant "Weltumsegler"
data.longDescription:
Our Weltumsegler family restaurant serves modern cuisine as well as classic fare such as schnitzel or curry wurst. The extensive menu menu has got something for every family member. You can, of course, also choose from a large selection of fresh salads, fruits, delicious desserts and cakes.

For Vegetarians and People suffering from Allergies
Be it lactose-free food or gluten-free meals – we will be delighted to prepare special menus that take care of your individual needs.

data.name: Remote-controlled Boats
data.longDescription:
Relax on the shores of the little lake at our Hansa Garden with our remote-controlled boats. You determine the course! Under Nessie’s watchful eyes… :-)

Particularly nice in May when the cherry trees are in full bloom.

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

data.name: Flying Dutchman
data.longDescription:
At home on the seas and in the air. Shake and swing – up to 24 metres high. Sky-high, mind-blowing!

Don't miss this fabulous attraction when you're at the Old-Time Fun Fair. Once aboard the pirate ship the rough seas of the world's oceans will shake and swing you 24m up into the air, back and forth. Beware of seasickness!

data.name: Escape of Novgorod
data.longDescription:
1,4 sec., 90 und 97 degrees are the facts of a sensational ride that will take passengers on a spine-tingling journey into the history of Novgorod.

From the depths of sinister walls the star of the Kataplektor class shoots into the light. Adrenaline junkies will love it!

The painstakingly designed story of the "Escape of Novgorod" will put even the most hardened coaster enthusiast under its spell. Hop on and experience this one-of-a-kind, never-seen-before concept melding a coaster placed inside a dark building, a themed dark ride laden with special effects, a state-of-the-art launched coaster accelerating to 100km/h in 1.4 seconds, an "open-air" roller coaster and a coaster featuring the steepest drop in the dark of all roller coasters in the world - steeper than vertical.

Visit us on Youtube!
data.shortDescription: From the depths of sinister walls the star of the Kataplektor class shoots into the light. Adrenaline junkies will love it!
data.metaDescription: The “Escape of Novgorod” is a roller coaster of the Kataplektor class: 1.4 sec., 90 degrees and 97 degrees are the facts of a sensational ride that will take riders on a spine-tingling journey into the history of Novgorod
data.rideDescription:
Fast paced thrill ride. Launch coaster featuring a vertical ascent and descent, quick turns, sudden drops, a heartline-roll and hard braking. Ride includes periods of darkness with light and sound effects and pop up characters.

If the train comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 25 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 30 minutes.

themeworlds.longDescription:
What times they were when the rough people from the far North went aboard their dragon boats to sail the world’s oceans.

Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.

data.name: Fondaco dei Tedeschi
data.longDescription:
German merchants first had to present their goods at the “Fondaco dei Tedeschi”, a trading base of German merchants in Venice, and were only allowed to sell them under the supervision of the powerful city that once dominated a large part of the Mediterranean Sea.

The new indoor attraction offers exciting join-in fun, two spine-tingling free-fall slides and a huge softball shooting area with 16 cannons.

You need a break in between all the playing and romping about? Visit the café bar and relax with a cappuccino and home-made cakes. If you prefer to chill out and surf the web, you’ll sure find a place in our new lounge that offers free Wi-Fi.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.longDescription:
In unserer Gamble Hall können Sie Ihr Geschick und vor allem Ihr Glück an verschiedenen Spielautomaten auf die Probe stellen.

Die Gamble Hall kann 2021 leider nicht geöffnet werden. Sollten Sie noch bestehende Gewinnpunkte einlösen wollen, so ist dies letztmalig noch in 2022 möglich. Ab 2023 können Gewinnpunkte nur noch während der laufenden Saison eingelöst werden.

themeworlds.name: Bonanza City
themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

data.name: Wristbands noting their heights
data.longDescription:
For safety reasons and to comply with TÜV regulations, height requirements apply at some of our attractions.

Our employees have been instructed to check the height at the respective attractions and re-measure children if necessary.

Alternatively, children can opt for a wristband noting their height. Just approach our staff at the Service Centre. They will measure them and hand them a wristband. Present it at the attractions and off they go on the ride!

This will save you precious time at the attractions – time that you can then fill with wonderful HANSA-PARK moments.

... and the eagle is circling above.

themeworlds.name: Bonanza City
themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

themeworlds.name: Lumberjacks' Camp
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Face the demon from Russia. Be catapulted into the air. Emerge from the horror of old walls towards the sky. After the ride: Pale. Numb. Ecstatic. Not everyone manages that.

Don’t you dare, Mr Escape of Novgorod!

themeworlds.name: Land of the Vikings
themeworlds.shortDescription: Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.
themeworlds.longDescription:
What times they were when the rough people from the far North went aboard their dragon boats to sail the world’s oceans.

Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.

data.name: HANSA-PARK Parade
data.longDescription:
Every afternoon the ambassadors of happiness take a tour through the Park – if the weather is decent.

Note: The Parade starts at Kungstorget, then turns towards Tienda del Mar, passes the Escape of Novgorod and heads for the Hansa Carousel. From there the Parade returns to Kungstorget via the Lumberjacks‘ Camp.

For safety reasons the HANSA-PARK parade will not take place if the weather is wet or stormy.
data.shortDescription: Every afternoon the ambassadors of happiness take a tour through the Park – if the weather is decent.
data.metaDescription: Every afternoon at 3 pm (in dry weather only) it’s time for the HANSA-PARK Parade – a colourful parade that winds its way through HANSA-PARK

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

themeworlds.name: Children's World
themeworlds.shortDescription: Children always want to try out everything. That’s why there’s HANSA-PARK because that’s where they can and especially so in our Children’s World!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Some never want to leave the Ball House.
Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

Of course, children want to try out everything.

Well, that’s why there’s HANSA-PARK where they have all the time in the world to do just that.

All day long!

data.name: Hanse Café
data.longDescription: Our HANSE Café is located in our Service Centre right next to the entrance area, adjacent to our Information Office. You are hungry but don’t want to waste a second of your time at HANSA-PARK? Go to our HANSE Café to get a breakfast “to-go”. Choose from a range of delicious pretzels, sandwiches freshly produced at our sandwich factory and many more yummy goodies.
data.shortDescription: You’re supposed to breakfast like a king …
data.metaDescription: Start your day at HANSA-PARK with a sumptuous breakfast at our Hansa Café.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: HANSA Swing Ride
data.longDescription:
HANSA-PARK invites you to enjoy a ride on the HANSA Swing Ride - a wave rider that has been lovingly designed with an eye for detail.

Located close to the HANSA Carousel, the ride completes the existing and future façades of the “The Hanseatic League in Europe”. While the façades of the houses built in traditional style provide an authentic, classic ambience, the HANSA Swing Ride conveys the intriguing charm of the Hanseatic cities back then and now: unobtrusive and yet full of life, easy-going, steadfast and open. The ride offers timeless flying fun for the whole family.

data.name: HANSA Carousel
data.longDescription:
Each round takes children to another level of happiness. The Hansa is back - 36 pictures show scenes of the most important Hanseatic cities. An album that brings Hanseatic history to life.

Seating more than 40 riders, featuring 24 horses moving up and down - all endowed with real horse hair tails and leather horse's harnesses - and a carriage that moves along with the carousel like the horse's, this merry-go-round can also be driven manually.
Though designed based on 18th century models, the magnificent carousel is equipped with state-of-the-art technology. In the evening it is a real eye catcher when it shines brightly with the fairy light created by over 1,000 light bulbs. But HANSA-PARK wouldn't be HANSA-PARK if this jewel of a merry-go-round didn't feature something very special to make it globally unique.

36 pictures adorn the inside walls of the carousel, which show typical scenes of the most important Hanseatic cities with their trading and townhouses as well as merchant offices [kontors] from the 14th, 15th and 16th century. The hand-painted pictures were chosen by the mayors of the cities depicted on them - a proud 'yes' to the cities' common history. "The Hansa is on the move again" - a befitting statement when you watch the carousel doing its rounds.

data.name: Hansa merchant offices [kontors]
data.longDescription:
Drop by at our Hansa merchant offices [kontors] where you’ll find whatever your heart may wish for, be it toys for the little ones or souvenirs for your loved ones at home. Perhaps a little souvenir for yourself?

You would like to listen to the sound of KÄRNAN, The Little Tsar or The Midgard Serpent at home? Go to our HANSE-KONTOR where you can get each ride attraction’s soundtrack on CD.

The shop also stocks necessities. Forgot to take along your sun lotion, lighter or umbrella for “maybe” rain? Don’t worry, the shop has got it all.

Take your pick from a variety of cooled drinks and sweet treats to ensure that the ride home will make an already perfect day even more perfect.

data.name: "HIGHLANDER"
data.longDescription:
HANSA-PARK’s stand-alone freefall tower Highlander is set to break all (previous) records in Germany, on the European continent and worldwide.

[nbsp]

  • Highest and fastest Gyrodrop Tower of the world with a height of 120 m (394 feet) and a speed of 120 km/h (75 mph)
  • 103 meter-drop – breaking all previous records
  • Worldwide highest Gyrodrop tower with tilting seats

Facts

Ride will go into operationduring the 2019-season
ManufacturerFuntime GmbH, Wien
InspectionTÜV Süd
Height120 meters / 394 feet
Height above mean sea level149 meters / 489 feet
Length of drop103 meters / 334 feet
Speed120 km/h[nbsp] / 75 mph
Number of seats24 seats
Type of barsshoulder bars
Special featurestilting seats
Length of foundation piles28 meters / 92 feet
MusicHighlander
composed by Andreas Kübler und Sebastian Kübler of IMAscore

[nbsp]

HANSA-PARK’s Highlander is the park’s exclamation mark towering over the entire Bay of Lübeck. A must-do attraction for those wanting to combine a spectacular view with an ultimate freefall experience.

[nbsp]

And there is even more:

The „Highlander“ is an essential part of the park’s theme-area “Beautiful Britain”, which include the park’s highly appreciated classical coaster Nessie as well. “Beautiful Britain”[nbsp] introduce HANSA-PARKs guests to Scotland and to one of its most impressive castles Eilean Donan Castle.
data.metaDescription: HIGHLANDER im HANSA-PARK – der neue, freistehende Freifallturm am Meer pulverisiert alle bisherigen Rekorde in Deutschland, auf dem ganzen Kontinent und in der Welt
data.rideDescription:
Vertical lift to a height of over 100m in a rotating gondola followed by a vertical drop with a top falling speed of about 120 km/h. The seats are forward-tiltable by up to 30°.

If the gondola stops after the ride has started, riders must wait for the operating staff’s instructions before they are allowed to exit the ride. At the worst, the ride may stop at the highest position, i.e. over 100m up in the air.
If the gondola stops after the ride has started, the free fall is triggered as if it was a “normal” ride and magnetic brakes will stop the gondola in a safe slow-down. This process may take up to 45 minutes.

themeworlds.longDescription: Lose yourself in the beautiful world of Scotland and give in to the charm of Eilean Donan Castle. Expect spine-tingling fun of the finest! In the centre of the theme world, you’ll find the Highlander - a 120m-tall gyro drop tower that offers a breathtaking view of the Baltic sea and the surrounding area. Get ready for the ultimate free fall! Adjacent to the Highlander - or rather surrounding it - is Nessie, our traditional roller coaster. Right next to Nessie and always ready for a Rendezvous in the Loop: The Royal Scotsman.

data.name: Historical Steam Locomotive No. 8
data.longDescription:
Born in 1907, but you wouldn’t guess that when you see the Steam Locomotive No. 8. Hanomag built it in the last century.

Painted in green, black, red and gold, it is a majestic locomotive that is full of surprises for all the big and small engine drivers who have always dreamed of standing in the cab of a small-gauge steam locomotive.

There you can really let off steam. Press the speed control, listen to the steam engine work and hear the bell chime. And when you close your eyes and listen to the driving noises, you’ll feel transported back to the times when the steam locomotive with internal operating number 8 was on duty in Georgsmarienhütte together with its sister locomotives.
data.shortDescription: Feel like letting off some steam?
data.metaDescription: Feel transported back to the times of the steam locomotive? Our nostalgic train does indeed invoke such feelings. Lean back, forget the world around you and enjoy the magic of the past.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: The Navajo Trail High-Rope Garden
data.longDescription:
The Navajo Trail high-rope garden and obstacle course will challenge you with more than 25 skill exercises you won't find in any other high-rope garden. The Indian-themed attraction features an obstacle route that is over 200m long and up to 10m high.

Special features of the high-rope garden:

  • A new, patented safety system
  • No safety hooks have to be put on when changing to a new exercise. Very high safety standards as the high-rope garden cannot be exited anywhere.
  • No safety helmet required
  • Minimum height is 1.10m only because special child safety belts are used
  • Leads across water
  • Can also be used when it's dark as all route sections are lighted
  • No additional costs (included in the normal entrance fee)
  • Biggest safety belt sizes available:
    • Belly circumference: max. 140 cm
    • Leg circumference: max. 80 cm
    • Upper body, from belly to shoulder: max. 90 cm
data.shortDescription: It has no safety net, yet it’s completely safe. Step by step you’ll climb up until you are ten metres above the ground where challenging obstacles wait to be mastered.
data.metaDescription: The Navajo Trail High-Rope Garden at HANSA-PARK is included in the entrance fee. It is 200m long and features more than 25 skill exercises 10m high in the air.
data.rideDescription:
High rope course according to DIN EN 15567 at a height of up to 11 meters, partly crossing water, featuring various degrees of difficulty.
If unable to finish the course please refer to our staff. You will then be assisted at a max. height of 11 meters. This may take up to 30 minutes.

themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.name: Holstein Tower
data.longDescription: Since 1987 a slim white needle has pointed upwards into the white-blue North German sky. The landmark on the Baltic Sea coast stands 100m tall, and blowing in the wind on its top is a giant flag of the Federal State of Schleswig-Holstein measuring an unbelievable 30 square metres in size. The viewing gallery with floor-to-ceiling windows, that looks as if it comes straight from the future, goes upward with rotating movements allowing guests a fantastic view of the overwhelmingly beautiful landscape of the Holstein lake district, beyond the Lübeck Bay all the way to Mecklenburg – an old world re-discovered from a new perspective.
data.shortDescription: Rotate your way up the tower and enjoy a spectacular view from a height of 100m. The entire Hansa world is at your feet. And on top flies the flag of Schleswig-Holstein.
data.metaDescription: Since 1987 HANSA-PARK’s guests have enjoyed a spectacular view of the Park and the glittering Baltic Sea of the Bay of Lübeck from the Holstein Tower at HANSA-PARK, a roughly 100m-high viewing tower.

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

data.name: Dogs
data.longDescription:
Your dog is, of course, welcome in the park. However please keep it on a lead and carry a cleaning set along. You can obtain the cost-free set from the staff at the box offices and entrance control.

“Water refuelling stations” for dogs can be found throughout the park.

Please note that, for safety reasons, dogs are prohibited in our shows and on our ride attractions. We hope to have your understanding that dogs are not allowed in our souvenir shops and in restaurant areas where food is presented uncovered, e.g. in the buffet area.

data.name: Indian River
data.longDescription:
Grab the paddle, white brother! And when you are exhausted, dad will surely push you a bit. Howgh!

Let your children join us on an interactive canoeing trip into the land of the Wild West Indians past croaking frogs and authentic-looking teepees.

Leave the Wild Water Ride and Super Splash to the less sporty guests and choose the Indian River if you prefer activity to idleness because our Baltic Sea Indians have to paddle themselves to master this attraction.

Just to make sure that parents aren’t afraid of the big bear when the young warriors are out on their mission, they are allowed to accompany them on a path along the “canyon”. Grab this perfect opportunity and take great pictures or arrange for a photo-shooting session!

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

Welcome, gringo!

data.name: Italian Restaurant "L'Artista"
data.longDescription:
Come to our Italian restaurant "L'Artista" and savour Luigi's Italian and vegetarian dishes. His sumptuous pizza [&] pasta range is complemented by changing special offers. A buffet offering a wide selection of salads and antipasti is also waiting to be stormed.

Or pop in in the afternoon, have a cappuccino and enjoy freshly made cake specialities and, as a cost-free extra, take in the captivating view of our Old-Time Fun Fair. Numerous ride attractions are located very close by. The romantic among you have the option to ride a boat through a sea of flowers to the accompaniment of waltz music. Or do you want to revive childhood memories? Ride the Flying Swing Ride. Right next to the restaurant, you'll find our open-air stage - the perfect platform to perform all kinds of shows.

For Vegetarians and People suffering from Allergies
Be it lactose-free food or gluten-free meals – we will be delighted to prepare special menus that take care of your individual needs.
data.shortDescription: Home-made pizza [&] pasta
data.metaDescription: Go to our Italian restaurant “L’Artista” if you love home-made pizza & pasta. Salad and antipasti are, of course, available too.

themeworlds.name: Old-Time Fun Fair
themeworlds.shortDescription: Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.

We captured the atmosphere of a nostalgic fairground and added some attractions: the Safari Jeeps, the Flying Dutchman and the Flower Magic Boat Tour.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

data.name: Joe's Cowboy Cookout Barbecue
data.longDescription: Are you a fan of the Wild West? Then Joe’s Grill in the Wild West town of Bonanza City is just the thing. After a hard day’s work of washing gold or riding the Pony Express tuck into the freshly cooked food. Make yourself at home on the rustic tree trunk benches like the cattle traders used to long ago and take in the atmosphere of the Wild West.

data.name: KÄRNAPULTEN
data.longDescription: Located right next to KÄRNAN, KÄRNAPULTEN is there to defend the fortress and its tower. If you want to help, hop on the Sky Fly manufactured by Gerstlauer and start your adventure. Be it a heroic flight manoeuvre up to 22m up in the air, daring somersaults or a fearless recon flight - you decide how you want to protect KÄRNAN. Interactive fun for the whole family that makes nerves tingle and challenges old and young alike. Riders must be taller than 125cm!

Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

data.name: Kiddie Camp
data.longDescription:
Our Kiddie Camp is fully roofed so that you can play there in any weather.

Jump on hot trucks, racy locomotives or be a cool chauffeur yourself. Mum and Dad can relax at the “Riva-Bar” and replenish their energy reserves while you are enjoying a game of softball shooting!

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

themeworlds.longDescription:
Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.

We captured the atmosphere of a nostalgic fairground and added some attractions: the Safari Jeeps, the Flying Dutchman and the Flower Magic Boat Tour.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

data.name: Children’s Face Painting
data.longDescription:
You’ve always wanted to be a hissing tiger, a dangerous buccaneer or a beautiful princess? Now you can! Our new magic fun faces make it possible!

The magic fun faces are a great way to remember a wonderful day spent at HANSA-PARK as they can last for up to a week. They are fun for young and old alike!

We also offer traditional children’s face painting at certain times. Look out for a notice posted at the make-up point.
You can also opt to get one of the popular temporary tattoos. Choose from a wide variety of motives, for example anchors, stars, horse or football, and enjoy your tattoo for about 3-4 days.
data.shortDescription: Open at weekends, on bank/public holidays and in the school holidays.
data.metaDescription: At HANSA-PARK’s Make-up Point children can either have their face painted or get an awesome tattoo “with an expiry date”.

themeworlds.name: Children's World
themeworlds.shortDescription: Children always want to try out everything. That’s why there’s HANSA-PARK because that’s where they can and especially so in our Children’s World!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Some never want to leave the Ball House.
Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

Of course, children want to try out everything.

Well, that’s why there’s HANSA-PARK where they have all the time in the world to do just that.

All day long!

data.name: Land of the Native Americans

Have you ever sat by the campfire like a real Native American and baked skewered bread? No? Well, it’s high time you do! At the Land of the Native Americans, you’re hot on Winnetou’s heels.

Apart from jewellery you can also buy bows and arrows or tomahawks.

themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.name: Cog Ship Ride
data.longDescription:
Children sailing the seas aboard bulbous cargo ships deployed in the heydays of the Hanseatic League. Up and down the waves, pushed by the wind.

The centre of the Old-Time Fun Fair is occupied by the Cog Ship carousel, towered by a bizarre fish that rotates on a globe symbolising the world and its oceans. The beautiful glass painting and gilding of the fish make it shimmer and shine in all the colours of the rainbow – a truly magnificent sight.

themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Wheelchair Hire
data.longDescription:
For visitors with mobility issues. Limited availability -please book in advance.

A deposit is required and you will have to provide your name and address. Please approach our staff at Holstentor.
data.shortDescription: There is no need for you to bring along your own transport. Simply hire one of our nine new, free- of-charge wheelchairs. Go to the main entrance, give your personal details to the staff, pay a refundable deposit and off you go on the handy help.
data.metaDescription: Simply hire one of our nine new, free- of-charge wheelchairs.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Feedback - HANSA-PARK Speaking Trumpet
data.longDescription:
You are in the Park and want to tell us something? Use the HANSA-PARK speaking trumpet to contact us directly and digitally.

data.name: Road Locomotive
data.longDescription:
Knowledge you can touch and experience – the Road Locomotive at HANSA-PARK

Have you ever seen a road locomotive? This type of vehicle was used in the 19th century by farmers, miners and in other industries. A blast from the past that you can touch. It also makes for a perfect photo!

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

data.name: Nessie
data.longDescription:
It's airtime mates! Some may think, “Well that’s nothing new”. Nessie! Racy rendezvous in the loop.

Butterflies in your stomach! Slowly climbing towards the sky, then a plunge upside-down into the giant loop of the super roller coaster Nessie - girls scream, men stop breathing! But watch out: one single ride and you’re hooked! Suspense, goose pimples and non-stop thrill are the name of the game at HANSA-PARK. Sensational and not to be found in any other leisure park in the world – that’s Nessie´s ‘Rendezvous in the Loop’ with the Royal Scotsman.

data.rideDescription:
Fast paced roller coaster featuring steep drops, one loop and hard barking. Rides includes period of darkness with light and sound effects.

If the train comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 26 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 30 minutes.

themeworlds.name: Beautiful Britain
themeworlds.longDescription: Lose yourself in the beautiful world of Scotland and give in to the charm of Eilean Donan Castle. Expect spine-tingling fun of the finest! In the centre of the theme world, you’ll find the Highlander - a 120m-tall gyro drop tower that offers a breathtaking view of the Baltic sea and the surrounding area. Get ready for the ultimate free fall! Adjacent to the Highlander - or rather surrounding it - is Nessie, our traditional roller coaster. Right next to Nessie and always ready for a Rendezvous in the Loop: The Royal Scotsman.

data.name: Odin's Travels through the Sky
data.longDescription:
Fun in the air for the happy-go-lucky! Towards the sun at 15km/h - seven metres high. The Germanic deity says hello.

The bucket seats can comfortably accommodate six children, the lap bars close gently and safely, music adds extra excitement - and off the platform with the little daredevils "shoots" towards the sun - at a breathtaking speed of 15 kilometres per hour, a full seven metres high. It glides back to the earth, soft as butter, bounces up and down a few more times - and spills out cheering girls and boys who feel like taking off into the air aboard a Viking boat right away.

data.name: Pony Express
data.longDescription:
At home in the saddle. Up-and-coming cowboys will find heaven on earth. Go West, young man!

Take the Pony Express and go on an exhilarating trip into the prairie. Big cowboys can seat the tiniest tots in specially designed ‘children’s saddles’ in front of them. That’s double the fun! Pass by the wagon fort or the old gold diggers’ cemetery - a rather spooky affair.
data.shortDescription: At home in the saddle. Up-and-coming cowboys will find heaven on earth. Go West, young man!
data.metaDescription: Guests taking the Pony Post will be in for an exciting trip into the prairie. Have your gun at the ready – many interactive targets are waiting for you…
data.rideDescription:
Interactive target shooting ride on wooden horses. Ride features sudden movements when being started and includes periods of darkness.

If the ride comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until ride starts again or until being escorted out. Hold on to handles or reins at all times.

themeworlds.name: Bonanza City
themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

data.name: Mail Coach
data.longDescription:
Don’t dare to sit on the horse on your own? Take the stagecoach!

Trace America’s Wild West in a stagecoach! Explore the stagecoach and make yourself familiar with the wooden horse as it will be the one carrying you through the Wild West town of Bonanza City. And should you lose control over your horse, just take the emergency slide…

data.name: Pow Wow
data.longDescription:
A dance around the totem pole. Hold on tight if the jugs suddenly go mad. Thoroughly shaken and stirred well!

Pow Wow is the name of a traditional folk dance in North America which sees dancers moving in a circle to a special rhythm. This ride attraction was named after it. 12 gondolas, modelled after Native American clay jugs, accommodate a family of five. They whirl you around gently yet fast and take you on an exciting ride on three platforms, each rotating at different speeds, spinning around a totem pole on top of which sits a giant eagle. You can even set your own speed: just spin the handwheel in the centre of your gondola to increase or reduce the pace! Like many other attractions at HANSA-PARK, the Pow Wow is roofed so the whole family can enjoy it in any weather conditions.

themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

themeworlds.longDescription:
Racy, racy - that moment in time when the two roller coasters meet in the air. While Nessie goes around in a loop, the Royal Scotsman speeds right through the centre. A roller coaster rendezvous!

And then a peek into tomorrow’s world: Intergalactic stop-and-go at the Space Scooter. Forget butterflies in the stomach; it’s more like centipedes crawling around...

...or rather like centipedes dancing Rock 'n’ Roll.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Raucherinsel Space Race / Werkstatt-Tor
data.longDescription:
Als Familienpark liegt uns besonders das Wohl unserer kleinen Gäste am Herzen. Aus diesem Grund gibt es bei uns Raucherinseln. Bitte rauchen Sie nur in diesen Bereichen.

Außerhalb der Raucherinseln ist das Rauchen nicht erlaubt. Dies gilt auch für E-Zigaretten.

Sie finden alle Raucherinseln auf unserem Parkplan: Download

themeworlds.name: Thrill Rides
themeworlds.shortDescription: Racy, racy - that moment in time when the two roller coasters meet in the air. While Nessie goes around in a loop, the Royal Scotsman speeds right through the centre. A roller coaster rendezvous!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Racy, racy - that moment in time when the two roller coasters meet in the air. While Nessie goes around in a loop, the Royal Scotsman speeds right through the centre. A roller coaster rendezvous!

And then a peek into tomorrow’s world: Intergalactic stop-and-go at the Space Scooter. Forget butterflies in the stomach; it’s more like centipedes crawling around...

...or rather like centipedes dancing Rock 'n’ Roll.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

themeworlds.name: Water Fun
themeworlds.shortDescription: There’s no fun without a few splashes. Droplets must fly and glitter in the sun. No matter whether you race down the Super Splash jump or dance in the crazy fountains at the Water Garden.
themeworlds.longDescription:
There’s no fun without a few splashes. Droplets must fly and glitter in the sun. No matter whether you race down the Super Splash jump or dance in the crazy fountains at the Water Garden.

Cool, man. The more so when it’s hot outside!

data.name: Smoking Areas
data.longDescription:
As a family park the well-being of our little guests is of foremost importance to us. That is why we have established designated smoking areas in the Park. Please smoke in these designated areas only.

Smoking and the use of e-cigarettes is permitted in the designated areas only.

Our Park map shows the designated smoking areas: download map

data.name: Rain Dance
data.longDescription: The rain dance ceremony is performed to call the rain. Help the Native Americans and join their dance to chase away the evil spirits. With a bit of luck you’ll become a member of their tribe. But watch out - you may get wet in the process…
data.shortDescription: Test your spiritual abilities
data.metaDescription: Not far from the Land of the Wild West Indians HANSA-PARK guests can test their spiritual abilities in a rain dance ceremony. But beware! If something goes wrong, guests will get each other wet!

themeworlds.name: Adventure Land
themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.
