data.name: Midgard Serpent Souvenir Shop
data.longDescription:
At the exit of our Midgard Serpent you’ll find our souvenir shop named EinarLei, where you cannot only get a personalised souvenir - a photograph of your ride on the Midgard Serpent - but the shop also offers a wide variety of great souvenirs from the legendary world of the Vikings.

Be it helmets, axes or shields - our EVA foam toy collection in the design of the Midgard Serpent leaves nothing to be desired.

Or get a Midgard Serpent T-shirt. The shop carries all sizes, for adults and children.

data.name: Royal Scotsman
data.longDescription: The Royal Scotsman is roller coaster fun for the whole family. It meets Nessie, our cult coaster, in a “rendezvous in the loop” and races through the newly designed Enchanting Britain themed area. Missing it when you visit HANSA-PARK would be a shame!
data.shortDescription: The Royal Scotsman is roller coaster fun for the whole family.
data.metaDescription: The Royal Scotsman, a cute family coaster, races through high-speed super roller coaster Nessie’s sky-high giant loop.
data.rideDescription:
Fast paced roller coaster including quick turns, steep descents and hard braking.

If the train comes to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use steep stairs at a maximum of appr. 12 meters height. The escorted exit may take up to 30 minutes.

themeworlds.name: Beautiful Britain
themeworlds.longDescription: Lose yourself in the beautiful world of Scotland and give in to the charm of Eilean Donan Castle. Expect spine-tingling fun of the finest! In the centre of the theme world, you’ll find the Highlander - a 120m-tall gyro drop tower that offers a breathtaking view of the Baltic sea and the surrounding area. Get ready for the ultimate free fall! Adjacent to the Highlander - or rather surrounding it - is Nessie, our traditional roller coaster. Right next to Nessie and always ready for a Rendezvous in the Loop: The Royal Scotsman.

data.name: Slides
data.longDescription:
Enough of walking? Take the slides instead!

Our slides at the lighthouse and in the climbing and exploring tower in the Wild West will shoot you down faster than your parents can buy French Fries.

themeworlds.name: Bonanza City
themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

themeworlds.name: Children's World
themeworlds.shortDescription: Children always want to try out everything. That’s why there’s HANSA-PARK because that’s where they can and especially so in our Children’s World!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Some never want to leave the Ball House.
Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

Of course, children want to try out everything.

Well, that’s why there’s HANSA-PARK where they have all the time in the world to do just that.

All day long!

data.name: Safari Jeeps
data.longDescription:
With determination and jungle fever Dr Livingstone‘s successors face the lions from up close in their Safari Jeeps. Hello Safari!

They look exactly like their big brothers in the African jungle – the Safari jeeps at HANSA-PARK. Striped black and white like zebras these jeeps zoom through the jungle scenery past wild lions, dangerous crocodiles, venomous snakes and huge elephants – a real adventure for the little explorers among you.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Saloon "Last Chance"
data.longDescription:
Hearty steaks and Mexican specialities are served at the Saloon "Last Chance" at Bonanza City where little cowgirls and cowboys feast on chicken nuggets or chicken balls. Salmon filet and locally sourced organic beef are also available.

A tasty piece of apple cake made with fresh apples, served with fresh cream and fruit sauce is a perfect dessert.

For Vegetarians and People suffering from Allergies
Be it lactose-free food or gluten-free meals – we will be delighted to prepare special menus that take care of your individual needs.
data.shortDescription: Right in the heart of the Wild West town of Bonanza City
data.metaDescription: Hearty steaks and Mexican specialities are served at the "Saloon Last Chance" at Bonanza City.

themeworlds.name: Bonanza City
themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

data.name: Space Scooter
data.longDescription:
Docking in the world of tomorrow. Who will be the fastest to reach the planets of our solar system? An intergalactic challenge!

While one of the pilots is steering and accelerating the vehicle through an intergalactic par course, it is the passenger's task to guide him or her safely to the altogether 9 docking stations at the planets of our solar system so to enable the pilot to complete the manoeuvre successfully with a 'faser'.

But watch out: of course, the other participants in the intergalactic space race want to dock, too, and at the same time try to prevent other game participants from scoring points...

An action game that demands fast reaction abilities, very good driving skills and high versatility as well as tactical skills and the ability to stay ahead of things at the right moment.

data.name: Spanish Gardens
data.longDescription:
Come to the Plaza del Mar where we have planted for you the flowers you find in southern Europe.

Go on an exotic-flower trip, visit our Spanish Gardens at the Plaza del Mar and be mesmerised by a beautiful carpet of flowers from that sun-kissed country while enjoying a stunning view of the brilliant Baltic Sea deep down.

themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Störtebeker's Sea Raid
data.longDescription:
Twirling on the wild water, the inflatable rafts shoot up and rotate across a 70m-long ramp.

Hop into rubber dinghies similar to the ones used for river rafting at the Grand Canyon and enjoy ‘Störtebeker's Sea Raid’: up and across an over 70m long ramp, where you have to savour the view of the sea swiftly because you’re only seconds away from shooting over a tip before you - seemingly aimlessly - circle into the depths of a canal with steep curves, like on a bobsled ride. During the lightning-fast, half-a-kilometre long ride down, the boats rotate in different directions several times and extremely fast – much like a crazy carousel dancing on wild waves.
data.shortDescription: Twirling on the wild water, the inflatable rafts shoot up and rotate across a 70m-long ramp.
data.metaDescription: Twirling on the wild water, the inflatable rafts shoot up and rotate across a 70m-long ramp.
data.rideDescription:
Bumper Boat- style ride featuring one steep ascent and quick turns. Ride includes section of darkness with light and sound effects.

If the boats come to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use a steep ramp at a maximum of appr. 18 meters height.

themeworlds.shortDescription: Children always want to try out everything. That’s why there’s HANSA-PARK because that’s where they can and especially so in our Children’s World!

All day long!

data.name: Stormy Dragon Boat Ride
data.longDescription:
Vikings battling wind and waves become one with their boat. Salt water is in their blood!

The tiny tots can look forward to experiencing their first true adventure at the pirate-inspired themed area: on a total ride length of about 160m the battle-tried Vikings will also speed down a drop from a height of 7m.
data.shortDescription: Vikings battling wind and waves become one with their boat. Salt water is in their blood!
data.metaDescription: In the Land of the Vikings, one of the Park’s themed areas, the tiny tots may well experience their first true water adventure - the Stormy Dragon Boat Ride.
data.rideDescription:
Boat ride featuring one steep drop.

If the boats come to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use a steep ramp at a maximum of appr. 8 meters height.

themeworlds.name: Land of the Vikings
themeworlds.shortDescription: Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.
themeworlds.longDescription:
What times they were when the rough people from the far North went aboard their dragon boats to sail the world’s oceans.

Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.

data.name: Super Splash
data.longDescription:
Take a splashing ride. Drop 20m down a slope with a gradient of 85% - that’s water fun of the finest! Splish splash, we are taking a bath!

Drop 20m down a slope with a gradient of 85% over a jump into a lake: this ride is so fast that the original American Wild Water Ride at HANSA-PARK seems like child’s play.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

themeworlds.name: Adventure Land
themeworlds.shortDescription: This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow-Wow for more relaxed moments.
themeworlds.longDescription:
This is the sovereign territory of the supersonic fans. Their passion has got a name: Crazy Mine. And Pow Wow for more relaxed moments.

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

data.name: Tahiti Trail
data.longDescription:
Funny parrots, colourful orchids, playful monkeys - the jungle of the South Seas holds many secrets.

Just what the very young explorers up to1.40 m in height are looking for: here, they can explore caves, swing on hanging vines and dash through trees - all in the footsteps of Georg Forster, the German who sailed to the South Seas with British seafarer, James Cook.

themeworlds.name: Children's World
themeworlds.shortDescription: Children always want to try out everything. That’s why there’s HANSA-PARK because that’s where they can and especially so in our Children’s World!
themeworlds.longDescription:
Some never want to leave the Ball House.
Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

Of course, children want to try out everything.

Well, that’s why there’s HANSA-PARK where they have all the time in the world to do just that.

All day long!

data.name: The Filling Station
data.longDescription:
Roaring hunger?

If you need to refuel in between rides, stop by at our refreshment kiosk just opposite of the Royal Scotsman.
data.shortDescription: Roaring hunger?
data.metaDescription: If you need to refuel in between rides, stop by at our refreshment kiosk just opposite of the Royal Scotsman.

themeworlds.name: Beautiful Britain
themeworlds.longDescription: Lose yourself in the beautiful world of Scotland and give in to the charm of Eilean Donan Castle. Expect spine-tingling fun of the finest! In the centre of the theme world, you’ll find the Highlander - a 120m-tall gyro drop tower that offers a breathtaking view of the Baltic sea and the surrounding area. Get ready for the ultimate free fall! Adjacent to the Highlander - or rather surrounding it - is Nessie, our traditional roller coaster. Right next to Nessie and always ready for a Rendezvous in the Loop: The Royal Scotsman.

data.name: Tienda del Mar
data.longDescription: “Viva España” is the motto at Tienda del Mar at the Plaza del Mar. Immerse yourself in the beautiful world of Spain and take home some of the enchanting flair. Our wide range of Spanish hats, Maraces rattles or lovely soft toys offers something for everyone!
data.metaDescription: “Viva España” is the motto at Tienda del Mar at the Plaza del Mar. Visit it and take home some of the enchanting flair.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Toiletten
data.longDescription:
It’s never far to a toilet at HANSA-PARK. In addition, special children’s toilets are available.

And for visiting wheelchair users, there are toilets located throughout the park:

  • Outside of the park at the main entrance area next to the Service Centre
  • Inside the park at the main entrance next to the Hanse Café
  • In the underpass to the Mirror Gallery
  • At the Tienda del Mar
  • At the Children’s World, next to the make-up point
  • At the Land of the Vikings

themeworlds.shortDescription: Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.

We captured the atmosphere of a nostalgic fairground and added some attractions: the Safari Jeeps, the Flying Dutchman and the Flower Magic Boat Tour.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

data.name: Lost Children Meeting Point
data.longDescription:
If your child has lost his or her way, a park employee will accompany him or her to our Service Centre at the main entrance.

Our service: at all our box offices and in the Information [&] Service Centre at the main entrance we offer high-quality key chains (lanyards) with little cards attached at just € 1, on which you can write down your name and telephone number. A free-of-charge alternative are our single-use HIPP Tyvek lost-child wristbands. The staff at our Service Centre will be happy to provide one. Unfortunately we cannot put out calls for children.

data.name: Dryers / Hairdryers
data.longDescription:
It’s no fun without a good share of spills on the Super Splash and the Wild Water Ride.

We make sure that you don’t have to walk around wet.

Use the full body dryer in front of the exit of our Super Splash to blow-dry your hair as well as your clothes. The dryer can accommodate up to four adults. At only € 2 you - and the rest of your family - can bathe in hot air until you feel warm and dry again.

“AWESOME!” is the name of the new show at the Arena del Mar, one of Europe’s leading variety theatres[nbsp]

data.name: Toilets
data.longDescription:
It’s never far to a toilet at HANSA-PARK. In addition, special children’s toilets are available.

And for visiting wheelchair users, there are toilets located throughout the park:

  • Outside of the park at the main entrance area next to the Service Centre
  • Inside the park at the main entrance next to the Hanse Café
  • In the underpass to the Mirror Gallery
  • At the Tienda del Mar
  • At the Children’s World, next to the make-up point
  • At the Land of the Vikings

data.name: Wave Rider

Surfing in the sky - ride merrily through the air in the arms of a giant octopus. Up and down, again and again...

Right next to the Fondaco dei Tedeschi hall the arms of a giant octopus are waiting to be boarded to swing you through the air - high up or deep down, almost touching the ground. themeworlds.longDescription:
Some never want to leave the Ball House.
Others are glued to their Mini Scooters.
And then there are those who‘ve discovered the Slides. Don’t you dare disturb them!

Of course, children want to try out everything.

Well, that’s why there’s HANSA-PARK where they have all the time in the world to do just that.

All day long!

data.name: Wickelraum Service-Center
data.longDescription:
Damit sich auch die Allerkleinsten rundum wohl fühlen!

Wickelräume und ruhige Orte zum Stillen gibt es im Service-Center am Haupteingang, im Kinderland neben dem Schminkplatz, am Kiosk im Wikingerland, neben der Tienda del Mar im spanischen Themenbereich und an der Wildwasserbahn im Holzfällerlager.
data.shortDescription: Damit sich auch die Allerkleinsten rundum wohl fühlen: Wickelräume und ruhige Orte zum Stillen gibt es im Service-Center am Haupteingang, im Kinderland neben dem Schminkplatz, am Kiosk im Wikingerland, neben der Tienda del Mar im spanischen Themenbereich und an der Wildwasserbahn im Holzfällerlager.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

themeworlds.name: Land of the Vikings
themeworlds.shortDescription: Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.
themeworlds.longDescription:
What times they were when the rough people from the far North went aboard their dragon boats to sail the world’s oceans.

Flying Orcas, Barracuda Slide, the Caravel Niña – boats and water are, of course, part of our world. After all, HANSA-PARK is Germany’s only event and family theme park by the sea.

themeworlds.name: Lumberjacks' Camp
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Face the demon from Russia. Be catapulted into the air. Emerge from the horror of old walls towards the sky. After the ride: Pale. Numb. Ecstatic. Not everyone manages that.

Don’t you dare, Mr Escape of Novgorod!

data.name: Nappy Changing Rooms
data.longDescription:
Infants and toddlers want to feel comfortable, too.

Nappy changing rooms and private corners to breastfeed your baby are available in the Service Centre at the main entrance, at the Children’s World next to the Make-up Point, at the refreshment kiosk in the Land of the Vikings, next to the Tienda del Mar and at the Wild Water Ride at the Lumberjacks’ Camp.

data.name: Re-entry into the Park
data.longDescription: Forgot something in the car? You can re-enter the Park on the day of your visit if you present a hand stamp and your valid entrance ticket to our staff. Please approach our service staff at Holstentor. They will put a stamp on your wrist before you leave the Park.

themeworlds.longDescription:

Winnetou’s friends are at home here too. They follow a track on the Navajo Trail, brave the dark in the Bear Cave and share their skewered bread with their white brothers at the campfire, ...

... and the eagle is circling above.

themeworlds.name: Hansa Garden
themeworlds.shortDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Sure, something is always on at HANSA-PARK. But the Park also offers beautiful corners that invite to take a break.
Take Hansa Garden, for instance. It‘s an oasis of peace.

Look down on the garden from the 100m-high Holstein Tower. Grab a remote control and steer one of the remote-controlled boats across the water, surrounded by the soothing green of the Garden. And very soon you’ll feel ready to continue exploring the Park – on the HANSA PARK Express.

A wonderful time!

themeworlds.name: Old-Time Fun Fair
themeworlds.shortDescription: Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Once upon a time the Chair-o-Plane Ride went round and round, fairground booth magic happened on a stage and looking at the distorted images of oneself in the Hall of Mirrors was a lot of fun.

We captured the atmosphere of a nostalgic fairground and added some attractions: the Safari Jeeps, the Flying Dutchman and the Flower Magic Boat Tour.

Relaxing to the sound of waltz music.

themeworlds.name: Thrill Rides

themeworlds.shortDescription: Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.
themeworlds.longDescription:
Here everything is where it’s supposed to be - steaks are at the saloon, gold is in the river and the sheriff in his office. The Pony Post is on time and if not, canoeing on the Indian River is a great alternative.

The blacksmith is forging horseshoes and the wood carver can’t be bothered by the campfire smoke wafting over from the Land of the Wild West Indians.

How about a photo wearing a colt? Any time - The Langenheim Brother's Photo Studio is just around the corner.

Welcome, gringo!

themeworlds.name: Fiesta del Mar
themeworlds.shortDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta!
themeworlds.longDescription: Where colourful buntings are flapping in the wind, the HANSA-PARK Parade passes by and the flowers have put on their best dress, you are right in the middle of a Spanish Fiesta! Come and join us at the Arena del Mar where fantastic acrobats show awe-inspiring routines. Or enjoy a fun-filled ride on the Barcos del Mar. Or take a relaxing break with a view of the ocean. Listen to the Talking Fountain, take a stroll through Tienda del Mar and walk along the Camino del Mar. In short: Feel like being in Mediterranean Spain right by the sea.

themeworlds.name: The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE
themeworlds.shortDescription: Over the coming years HANSA-PARK will gradually build a huge theme world keyed to the topic of “The HANSEATIC LEAGUE in EUROPE”.
themeworlds.longDescription:
The Hanseatic League was a medieval trading alliance formed by cities from all over Europe that provided its member cities with exotic goods and a stream of fresh ideas.

HANSA-PARK will recreate this colourful, international, lively Hanseatic League (also known as Hansa) over the next years. One location for a great idea, all at one glance: from Novgorod to Bruges, from Venice to Bergen, from Visby all the way to Lisbon.

The Hansa - that’s the future.

data.name: Viking Boat Trip
data.longDescription:
Under full sail - When real men ply the world’s oceans on their dragon boats, the going gets tough, seadog-tough!

Ahoy there landlubbers! Maritime riding fun at the Land of the Vikings. The smaller and bigger seafarers will love the action aboard a Viking ship. Steering the dragon boats through rough seas, cheered on by a Viking boy, who is riding the waves on the back of an orca whale, is not an easy feat and the youngest seafarers can ask a "weathered seadog" to help them.
data.shortDescription: Under full sail - When real men ply the world’s oceans on their dragon boats, the going gets tough, seadog-tough!
data.metaDescription: The Viking Boat Trip turns little children into tough seadogs. Plying the world’s oceans aboard dragon boats is every child’s dream, isn’t it?

data.name: Viking Boat “Viking Odin”
data.longDescription:
Fresh wind in your hair, salty air on your lips – do you feel drawn to the sea? Then the Viking Odin is where you want to be! The dream to sail your own ship comes true.

The “Viking Odin” is a slightly smaller replica of the Viking dragon boat excavated in Gokstad in Vestfold in 1880. The dragon head is not just adornment, it also serves to keep evil spirits away from the ship and her crew. According to legend, Leif Eriksen discovered America aboard such a ship 500 years before Columbus did.
data.shortDescription: Passenger ship from the time of the Vikings
data.metaDescription: Feel like a Viking aboard the Viking Odin and get an idea of how the Vikings felt when they sailed the seas. Odin makes sure that the waves won’t rise too high…

data.name: Wild Water Ride  - The Great Pike
data.longDescription:
Canoes upside down: Brave Russia’s water rapids in a log flume and take the 15-metre plunge! Refreshment included!

Get yourself a hollow log and set off on a roaring one-kilometre-long wild water ride set. After a mind-boggling plunge from a height of 15m into a narrow canal, the boat submerges into a shimmering fog of very fine water droplets.
data.shortDescription: Canoes upside down: Brave Russia’s water rapids in a log flume and take the 15-metre plunge! Refreshment included!
data.metaDescription: Canoes upside down: Brave Russia’s water rapids in a log flume and take the 15-metre plunge! Refreshment included!
data.rideDescription:
Rapid boat ride featuring two deep drops. Ride includes periods of darkness with light and sound effects.

If the boats come to a stop during the experience passengers are to remain seated until being told to exit or escorted by staff. Passengers may have to exit out of a banking position having to use a steep ramp at a maximum height of appr. 10 meters height.
